The most significant examples are those for which is a nuclear space; this comment is an abstract expression of the idea that consists of test functions and of the corresponding distributions. 

An example of a nuclear countably Hilbert space formula_14 and its dual formula_15 is the Schwartz space formula_16 and the space of tempered distributions formula_17, respectively, rigging the Hilbert space of square-integrable functions. As such, the rigged Hilbert space is given by
